You know how many times 
I could have cheated?

14:06.466 --> 14:08.010
Six... no seven.

14:08.027 --> 14:10.591
And you know two of them, 
and they would surprise you.

14:10.977 --> 14:13.031
3-C, let's do this. You ready?

14:13.046 --> 14:14.572
Should I just kick the door in?

14:14.587 --> 14:16.762
Those are really nice heels 
and you already lost the purse.

14:16.775 --> 14:18.691
Let's see if it's unlocked.

14:19.578 --> 14:21.442
It's unlocked.

14:21.457 --> 14:25.433
Okay, get in there 
and kick some spankable ass.

14:27.427 --> 14:29.202
Robin.

14:29.628 --> 14:32.021
- I'm the problem.
- What?

14:32.037 --> 14:33.360
You were right.

14:33.378 --> 14:34.753
I don't know how to be a girlfriend.

14:34.765 --> 14:36.530
I took the nicest guy in the world

14:36.547 --> 14:38.310
and I made him a cheater.

14:38.326 --> 14:40.923
Well, don't stand out here 
and beat yourself up.

14:40.937 --> 14:42.671
Get in there and beat Ted up.

14:42.686 --> 14:45.012
I'll handle the slutty kickboxer.

14:45.027 --> 14:47.211
Actually, I'll take Ted.

14:47.486 --> 14:50.202
- Let's do this.
- Bring it.

15:10.865 --> 15:12.553
What do you think you're...?

15:13.298 --> 15:14.490
Barney?

15:14.505 --> 15:17.491
Thank God you're here. 
Can you help with this? I need nails.

15:18.755 --> 15:21.451
Okay, I'm totally lost here. 
Where's Ted?

15:21.465 --> 15:23.330
Ted? He's at work.

15:23.345 --> 15:25.230
How did you get here?

15:25.558 --> 15:28.503
Awesome story. As per usual.

15:28.798 --> 15:31.542
How do you think Mr. Brady 
scored a babe like Carol?

15:31.558 --> 15:32.892
Solid point.

15:32.906 --> 15:35.812
- And she did have hair of gold.
- Yes, she did.

15:35.828 --> 15:37.923
Sorry, I forgot my binocs 
for Foxy Boxing.

15:37.938 --> 15:41.171
Whoo, looks like things just got 
a little foxier right here.

15:41.188 --> 15:42.843
Yes, they did. 
And you're just in time.

15:42.858 --> 15:46.843
Girls, I got to go, but I'm leaving you 
in very good, if slightly sullied hands.

15:46.856 --> 15:49.842
Don't go. We don't even know your name 
to look out for your buildings.

15:49.856 --> 15:51.920
Yeah, stay.

15:53.096 --> 15:54.902
Excuse us for one second.

15:55.686 --> 15:58.911
Okay, you were right-- 
the architect thing totally works.

15:58.928 --> 16:01.681
But I've got a girlfriend 
and I've got to get back to work.

16:01.698 --> 16:04.340
This project is getting 
harder and harder.

16:04.357 --> 16:06.472
- Yeah, you did.
- Yeah, had to.

16:06.486 --> 16:07.730
See ya.

16:09.006 --> 16:12.381
Sorry, my, uh... 
intern had to leave.

16:12.395 --> 16:14.271
Oh, well, that's too bad.

16:14.286 --> 16:16.372
I'm Anna, by the way.

16:17.926 --> 16:21.290
Ted Mosby... architect.

16:22.347 --> 16:25.482
But none of that acclaim means 
anything compared to the joy

16:25.496 --> 16:29.040
of seeing the sun rise 
over your first building.

16:30.797 --> 16:33.821
- Dude, dude, what are you doing?
- Galloping.

16:34.108 --> 16:38.301
All right, you proved it. The whole 
Ted Mosby, architect thing works.

16:38.315 --> 16:40.533
Architects rule! Whoo-hoo.

16:40.547 --> 16:43.683
Aren't you afraid a certain somebody 
might find out about this?

16:43.695 --> 16:45.733
I mean, this isn't you, Ted.

16:45.746 --> 16:47.771
It is tonight.

16:48.618 --> 16:50.671
And that led to a couple of hours

16:50.688 --> 16:54.642
that I cannot, as a gentleman, 
divulge to you.

16:54.658 --> 16:57.593
We did it right here, 
and here and here.

16:58.838 --> 17:01.693
But why would you use 
Ted's name?

17:01.705 --> 17:04.060
I've had some recent bad press 
on the World Wide Web.

17:04.076 --> 17:07.962
So I'm taking a T.O. on the whole 
"using my real name" thing.

17:08.867 --> 17:12.353
Oh, this is great. 
It wasn't Ted. Everything's okay.

17:12.367 --> 17:14.323
Everything isn't okay.

17:14.336 --> 17:18.692
Look at me. I'm acting crazy 
and jealous and paranoid.

17:18.707 --> 17:21.482
This is how people act 
in relationships.

17:21.497 --> 17:24.362
And that's why 
I avoid relationships.

17:24.948 --> 17:26.213
Well, guess what,

17:26.227 --> 17:29.431
I haven't been crazy or jealous 
or paranoid in months,

17:29.447 --> 17:32.731
and I really miss it.

17:33.085 --> 17:35.710
And thus ended this chapter of, 
"Let's pour our hearts out

17:35.726 --> 17:38.030
in the bedroom of Barney's 
one-night stand."

17:38.045 --> 17:40.010
Come on, let's go before 
she gets out of the shower.

17:40.027 --> 17:42.540
You're such a pig. 
You're not even going to say good-bye?

17:42.558 --> 17:46.251
I'll have you know 
I composed a lovely form letter

17:46.268 --> 17:48.682
for use in just such an occasion.

17:49.148 --> 17:51.840
Just fill out her name and then...

17:53.106 --> 17:54.763
Something  with a "A."

17:54.778 --> 17:57.432
A... A...

17:57.827 --> 18:00.400
I'll just put "resident."

18:02.335 --> 18:04.693
Go, go, go, go.

18:10.618 --> 18:12.780
Robin took a long walk that night.

18:12.796 --> 18:15.481
She thought about how opening 
yourself up to another person

18:15.498 --> 18:18.843
usually means opening yourself up 
to going a little crazy.

18:18.856 --> 18:22.653
She thought about how much easier 
it was just to be alone.

18:23.298 --> 18:25.521
And then she came to see me.

18:25.535 --> 18:29.991
# And I am nothing of a builder #

18:30.277 --> 18:34.953
# But here I dreamt I was an architect... #
Hey.

18:35.376 --> 18:36.723
Hey.

18:36.978 --> 18:39.692
- What are you doing here?
- I brought donuts.

18:39.706 --> 18:42.480
And I don't want to brag, 
but they're filled with jelly.

18:43.098 --> 18:44.452
Thanks.

18:46.895 --> 18:49.773
So, uh... how was your night?

18:49.788 --> 18:53.032
It was... fine. Nothing exciting.

18:53.048 --> 18:55.462
How was yours?

18:56.458 --> 18:59.291
You really want to hear about 
boring architect stuff?

18:59.307 --> 19:01.303
Yes, I do.

19:01.615 --> 19:04.093
I'm sorry about earlier.

19:04.547 --> 19:07.232
To tell you the truth, I never 
even saw all of Field of Dreams.

19:07.247 --> 19:09.662
I fell asleep half way through.

19:09.675 --> 19:11.873
What? The best part's 
the last 20 minutes.

19:11.887 --> 19:14.550
Well, maybe they should have moved that 
part up a little bit earlier, 'cause...

19:14.567 --> 19:16.620
You know what, um...

19:16.635 --> 19:19.583
What I'm trying to say is...

19:19.717 --> 19:22.922
I love being the person 
you bitch to.

19:23.908 --> 19:28.030
So how was your day, 
Mr. Architect?

19:28.047 --> 19:30.501
Oh, I like the way 
you say that.

19:31.298 --> 19:33.332
Hey, you want to see 
the building

19:33.345 --> 19:35.560
that will make every man 
in Spokane feel inadequate?

19:35.578 --> 19:37.260
Obviously.

19:38.316 --> 19:39.961
- Wow.
- Yeah.

19:39.975 --> 19:42.253
You know, you didn't mention 
all the foliage around the base.

19:42.265 --> 19:44.141
If you trim that back, 
the rest would look bigger.

19:44.156 --> 19:46.370
You don't have to tell me.

19:47.856 --> 19:51.632
And, um... just for fun, I've...

19:51.648 --> 19:55.511
I've sort of been working on my own idea 
of what I think the building should be.

19:59.928 --> 20:01.801
What do you think?

20:02.465 --> 20:06.590
You know that time we went to Spokane 
and I pointed out that skyscraper?

20:06.605 --> 20:09.381
That was the first building 
I ever designed.

20:09.398 --> 20:13.901
And that night was the first time 
I showed anyone my first drawing of it.

20:14.295 --> 20:15.920
Wow.

20:16.385 --> 20:18.851
Ted, this is amazing.

20:18.865 --> 20:20.781
Thanks.

20:22.175 --> 20:24.730
It's not like it will ever 
come to anything.

20:24.745 --> 20:26.501
I don't know.

20:26.826 --> 20:28.962
It might come to something.

20:29.176 --> 20:34.133
You know, girls find 
architects very hot.

20:37.786 --> 20:39.752
Okay,

20:39.765 --> 20:44.162
but I don't want you expecting 
78 stories or anything.

20:50.527 --> 20:52.641
"Dear Resident...

20:52.657 --> 20:55.571
The time we spent together, 
however long it was,

20:55.585 --> 20:57.443
meant the world to me.

20:57.455 --> 21:00.372
I would love to see you again, 
but unfortunately, I cannot.

21:00.387 --> 21:03.861
You see, I am a ghost.

21:03.878 --> 21:06.780
I can't only materialize 
once every decade

21:06.797 --> 21:09.300
on the anniversary of my death.

21:09.316 --> 21:12.452
I chose to spend my one day among 
the living with you,

21:12.467 --> 21:14.512
sweet... Resident.

21:14.526 --> 21:17.430
Perhaps we will meet again 
in another decade,

21:17.445 --> 21:19.751
provided you keep your figure.

21:19.766 --> 21:23.293
Until then, all my love 
from the beyond.

21:23.305 --> 21:25.020
Barney."

21:25.725 --> 21:27.630
Barney?

21:28.376 --> 21:31.340
Who the hell is Barney?

